        <selectionEntry id="c440-a9d0-445b-c2fd" name="Skorzenky&apos;s Commandos 150. Panzerbrigade" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="d62d-53fe-b9f1-19aa" name="Skorzenky&apos;s Commandos 150. Panzerbrigade" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">At the core of Skorzeny&apos;s battlegroups were the veteran commandos of 502. SS-Jagerbataillon (502nd SS-Light Infantry Battalion).</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Your Force includes one 150. Panzerbrigade Kampfgruppe, which is a Formation containing:
• 1	 HQ Unit of 2x MP40 SMG team from (LG157) for 3 points.
• 1	 Panther (late) Tank Platoon (LG360)
	 or Fallschirmjager Platoon (LG158)
• 1	 StuG Tank Platoon (LG247)
	 or Fallschirmjager Platoon (LG158)
• 0-1 Fallschirmjager Platoon (LG158)
• 0-1 7.5cm Tank-hunter Platoon (LG131)
• 0-1 12cm Mortar Platoon (LG172)
The Panther (Late) Tank Platoon, StuG Tank Platoon, and any Unit mounted in Softskin Transport in this Formation must use Enemy Disguises (see card).
(LFTF): The HQ Unit is a FallschirmjägerCompany HQ (LG157) from D-Day:German. It may take the Panzerfaust option.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Formation, Title, Limited (LFTF)</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
